Portugal Telecom denies Concert chosen . Portugal Telecom ( PT ) denied on Wednesday a newspaper report that it had opted for the British Telecom - MCI Communications Corp alliance Concert as its strategic partner . " No decision has yet been taken ( over the strategic partner ) , spokesman Jose Maria Amado told Reuters . Amado said a study on potential alliances being drawn up for Telecom by Morgan Grenfell and Arthur D . Little , and on which the state - controlled concern would base its opinion , was not yet ready . The company will make a recommendation but it is up to the government to take the final decision on the alliance . 
